<HEADLINE>
<P>
VETERAN NEWPORT POLICEMAN DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEWPORT BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Justin Allen (Al) Epstein, a 28-year Newport Beach police officer who received 
numerous letters of commendation over the years, died of leukemia Sunday at age 
63 at Hoag Hospital, the police department announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Epstein started on the force in 1953 as a patrol officer and later worked as a 
detective in the burglary and narcotics sections. But a department spokesman 
said he is best remembered for his long hours of effort in the vice and 
intelligence section, where he served eight years until his retirement in 1981. 
</P>
<P>
He won Officer of the Year honors in 1967. Then-Chief James Glavas lauded him, 
saying, "I know of no one in this department . . . who has exhibited more 
dedication and more enthusiasm for their work." 
</P>
<P>
Services will be conducted at 1 p.m. Sunday at Mount Sinai Mortuary and 
Memorial Park, 5950 Forest Lawn Drive in Los Angeles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Obituary 
</P>
