<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MUSIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Toronto Symphony to Tour Pacific Rim: Calling it the most ambitious 
international tour in its 67-year history, the Toronto Symphony Orchestra has 
announced a spring tour of the Pacific Rim. Covering 26 days and 11 cities, the 
tour will also include the first visit to Australia by a major Canadian 
orchestra. The tour begins in Vancouver on April 30 with a performance at the 
Orpheum Theatre, then travels to San Francisco for a concert at the Louise M. 
Davies Symphony Hall. After that, there will be concerts at four cities in 
Australia, three in Japan and single concerts in Singapore and Taiwan. CLAUDIA 
PUIG 
