<HEADLINE>
<P>
EL CAJON MAN KILLS WIFE, HIMSELF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An elderly man killed his wife and then shot himself to death Thursday in El 
Cajon, police reported. 
</P>
<P>
The dead couple were identified as Orville Gladstone Meland, 90, and Ruthe 
Bestic Dolan Meland, 73. They lived in a mobile home on East Main Street, the 
coroner's office said. 
</P>
<P>
Police said they received a call just after 10 a.m. about "a problem" at the 
couple's residence. 
</P>
<P>
When officers arrived, they knocked on the front door but no one answered. The 
door was unlocked and police went inside. Orville Meland was sitting in a chair 
with his back to the door. He had a bullet wound in the head and was dead. 
</P>
<P>
On the kitchen floor, they found Mrs. Meland covered with a blanket. She too 
had been shot in the head and was dead, according to police and the coroner's 
office. 
</P>
<P>
Police found a note apparently written by the elderly man that said the couple 
had been having problems, and that he had killed his wife and then was going to 
kill himself. 
</P>
</TEXT>
