<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 2 MEN, WOMAN ROB TARZANA JEWELRY STORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three robbers escaped with jewels worth hundreds of thousands of dollars from a 
Tarzana store just as its employees were closing up, Los Angeles police said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Two men and a woman entered Marcel's Unique Jewelry in the 19300 block of 
Ventura Boulevard about 6 p.m. Wednesday as two employees were closing for the 
night and the business' two safes were open, Detective Vic Morett said. 
</P>
<P>
The two men pointed guns at the employees and ordered them onto the floor. The 
robbers emptied both safes of a variety of jewelry and unset gems and left 
through the front door, Morett said. No one was injured. 
</P>
<P>
The value of the stolen merchandise has not been determined but Morett 
estimated that the loss could be in excess of $300,000, based on the wholesale 
cost of what was taken. 
</P>
