<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : SANTEE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A schoolteacher was arrested after 19 charges of child molestation were filed 
against him by the San Diego County district attorney's office. 
</P>
<P>
John Patrick Busker, 27, of La Mesa, surrendered to Sheriff's Detective Mary 
Stables in his attorney's office Wednesday about 4:30 p.m., Detective Dana 
Gassaway said. 
</P>
<P>
The charges stem from incidents that allegedly occurred at Chet F. Harritt 
Elementary School in Santee. In late November, nine girls, ages 8 through 11, 
complained that a "substitute teacher had touched them in areas that made them 
feel uncomfortable," Sheriff's Lt. Jerry Snow said. 
</P>
<P>
Busker was released Thursday on a $75,000 bond. He is scheduled for arraignment 
Wednesday. 
</P>
