<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
WALTERS PACES ANTELOPE VALLEY WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chris Walters scored a game-high 30 points and three other players from 
Antelope Valley High scored in double figures as the Antelopes defeated Crespi, 
79-63, in a nonleague boys' game Thursday at Crespi. 
</P>
<P>
Walters added 11 assists and teammate Jabbar Briggs scored 13 points for 
Antelope Valley (7-2). Center John Pletsch scored 13 points and had 12 rebounds 
for the Antelopes. 
</P>
<P>
Rasaan Hall scored a team-high 29 points for Crespi (5-6) and Matt Luderer 
handed out 10 assists. 
</P>
<P>
In other nonleague games: 
</P>
