<HEADLINE>
<P>
AUTOMOBILE ACCIDENT LITIGATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Clipboard researched by Susan Davis Greene, Dallas M. Jackson and Janice L. 
Jones / Los Angeles Times; Graphics by Doris Shields / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
County residents are the most litigious in the state, at least in terms of 
automobile accidents. Although more than three times as many such suits were 
filed in Los Angeles County, the Orange County mark of 485.57 suits filed per 
100,000 residents is the highest in the state. By comparison, the lowest rate 
among the 58 counties was 37.04 in Calaveras. 
</P>
<P>
Orange County ranked second last year, with a per 100,000 resident rate of 
484.13 while Los Angeles County had the highest rate, 506.90. But an 8.58 
decrease in suits in Los Angeles County between this year and last helped move 
Orange County into the top spot. 
</P>
<P>
Here's a look at how we compare to the four contiguous counties as well as the 
state, this year and last: 
