<TEXT>
<P>
Results of an autopsy performed Thursday on the body of Tommie Gray, starting 
nose tackle for the Cal State Northridge football team, will not be released 
until toxicological tests have been performed, according to the L.A. County 
coroner's office. 
</P>
<P>
The results of those tests will not be available for more than a week, a 
coroner's investigator said. 
</P>
<P>
Gray, 21, died late last Friday while visiting with friends at the University 
Park Apartments complex swimming pool. 
</P>
