<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Big Ten-bound Penn State has been sent a letter by Atlantic 10 officials, 
suggesting that the school leave the conference by June 30, the Pittsburgh 
Press reported. Penn State had announced Tuesday that it would join the Big 
Ten. 
</P>
<P>
The Atlantic 10's decision was reached Wednesday in a telephone conference call 
involving the athletic directors of the nine other conference schools, the 
newspaper reported. 
</P>
<P>
Penn State has said it intends to remain in the Atlantic 10 through the 1990-91 
season, but Atlantic 10 Commissioner Ron Bertovich, who is negotiating 
television contracts, said he doesn't like the Nittany Lions' lame-duck status. 
</P>
<P>
Penn State President Bryce Jordan has declined to reveal the school's plans 
concerning the Atlantic 10, saying, "I just wouldn't be interested in 
commenting until I saw the letter." 
</P>
</TEXT>
