<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIALEAH LOSES APPEAL ATTEMPT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TALLAHASSEE, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A state appeals court Thursday refused to reinstate Hialeah Park's pari-mutuel 
license, which was suspended after the track changed its racing schedule 
without permission. 
</P>
<P>
The 1st District Court of Appeal declined to lift the suspension ordered by the 
Department of Business Regulation. That means the track will be closed until at 
least Jan. 3, when a full state hearing is scheduled. 
</P>
<P>
Last week, the financially troubled South Florida thoroughbred track announced 
it would operate three days a week rather than the six days a week required 
under its license. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
