<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Dana Parsons and Mark I. Pinsky 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROOSEVELT: The Roosevelt Family name is inextricably linked with Panama. . . . 
Work on the Canal was begun during Teddy Roosevelt's administration. . . . 
James Roosevelt, a Newport Beach resident and a Democrat, is TR's grand-nephew 
and FDR's eldest son. . . . Of the Panama incursion, Roosevelt, who turns 82 on 
Saturday, says: "The important thing now is to think of the whole hemisphere, 
rather than (just) Panama. I wouldn't say I'm satisfied; I would say I'm 
anxious to see a more detailed and long-range program worked out." Dana Parsons 
and Mark I. Pinsky 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
UNITED STATES -- FOREIGN RELATIONS -- PANAMA; ROOSEVELT, JAMES; PANAMA CANAL; 
UNITED STATES -- FOREIGN POLICY -- CENTRAL AMERICA 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
