<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ORANGE; 
</P>
<P>
HIT-RUN DRIVER KILLS PEDESTRIAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 39-year-old woman was killed Thursday when she was struck by a hit-and-run 
driver as she crossed a street in Orange, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Officers said they are seeking the public's help in finding the driver who sped 
away after he ran his vehicle into Rosa Alvarez Calletano of Orange at about 
6:15 a.m. while she was walking in the crosswalk on Tustin Street at Adams 
Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
Orange police Sgt. Art Romo said police do not have a description of the driver 
or the car that struck the woman. 
</P>
<P>
Calletano's death caused a major traffic tie-up as officers converged to 
investigate the scene. Tustin Street, a major north-south thoroughfare near the 
Mall of Orange and parallel to the Costa Mesa Freeway, was closed during 
morning rush hours between Katella Avenue and Collins Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
"Cars (were) being rerouted back onto the freeway or into the residential 
streets around that section" of Tustin Street, Romo said. 
</P>
<P>
Investigators were hoping to find a witness to the accident, Romo said. He 
asked that anyone with information contact Detective Jim Pyne at (714) 532-0629 
or the Orange Police Department desk at (714) 532-0365. 
</P>
