<P>
BITTER COLD SHATTERS RECORDS; SNOW EXPECTED IN NORTH FLORIDA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Arctic cold wave shattered records in dozens of cities all over again today, 
icing parts of Texas with snow. Forecasters warned northern Florida to brace 
for a snowstorm. 
</P>
<P>
The bottom dropped out of the thermometer in Nebraska overnight when the 
mercury sank to 41 below zero at Scotts Bluff and Alliance. 
</P>
<P>
Cold weather records fell like snowflakes from the Rockies to the East Coast. 
</P>
<P>
They included 25 below at Goodland and Concordia, Kan.; 21 below in Topeka, 
Kan.; 23 below at Kansas City, Mo.; 28 below in Cheyenne, Wyo.; 15 below at 
Wichita, Kan.; 4 below at Tulsa; 23 below at Indianapolis; 20 below at Dayton 
and Cincinnati, Ohio, and 1 below at Binghamton, N.Y. 
</P>
<P>
The onrush of cold threw sleet, freezing and an inch of snow on Houston. 
</P>
